                              Privacy Statement

   Thank you for visiting the Federal Maritime Commission Website and
   reviewing our privacy policy. Our policy is clear: We will collect no
   personal information about you when you visit our website unless you
   chose to provide that information to us.

      You do not have to give us personal information merely to visit
     our site.

      We collect detailed information about you like your name, email
     address, etc. only if you specifically and knowingly provide it to
     us.

      When we ask you to identify yourself we provide an explanation.

      We do not give, sell or transfer any personal information to a
     third party.

      We do not enable "cookies." (A "cookie" is a file placed on your
     hard drive by a Web site that allows it to monitor your use of the
     site, usually without your knowledge.)

   The information we receive depends upon what you do when visiting our
   site. You may decide to send us personally-identifying information, for
   example, in an electronic mail message, or in filing Form FMC-1.
   Personally-identifiable information included in e-mails or forms will
   only be used for the purposes provided.


